
. ***Source: Nick Bloom, November 2010, nbloom@stanford.edu
. *This file investigates the sampling bias in the HH IT survey
. *It tests if our sample of management firms with accounting data (those for w
> hich we use in Table 6) has differential HH matching. 
. 
. 
. u replicate,replace

. qui tab cty,gen(cc)

. *Matched are the sites which are in HH (single or one of multi-matches)
. gen matched=(s_c~=.)

. so company_code year

. gen labp=ly-le
(352 missing values generated)

. *Collapse for the cross-sectional matching regression
. collapse lemp peeps matched du_usa_mu du_oth_mu cc* labp ldegree_t* public* s
> ic,by(company_code)

. cap estimates drop *

